      "span_text": "The activation of G proteins via ␤ARs plays a key role in the regulation of cardiac contractility. We therefore analyzed the induction of cAMP synthesis and contractility in response to the ␤AR agonist isoproterenol (ISO) in H10 cells, NRCM, and ARCM overexpressing G␤ 1 WT␥ 2 or G␤ 1 H266L␥ 2 at a similar level."
